{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Use British English|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = Isaac Hatch | image = | country = England | fullname = Isaac Hatch | nickname = | birth_date = c.1760 | birth_place = [[England]] | batting = unknown hand | bowling = underarm: unknown hand and type | role = batsman | club1 = [[Kent county cricket teams|Kent]] | year1 = c.1781–1790 | club2 = | year2 = | date = 20 March | year = 2013 | columns = 0 | source = [[Arthur Haygarth]] }}
'''Isaac Hatch''' (dates unknown) was an English [[first-class cricket|first-class]] [[cricket]]er who was active in the 1780s. He had [[Amateur status in first-class cricket|amateur status]] and played for [[Kent county cricket teams|Kent]]. He was recorded playing for Kent against [[White Conduit Club]] at [[White Conduit Fields]] in June 1786, scoring 0 and 7.<ref>Haygarth, p.64.</ref><ref name="CA74">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/0/74.html |publisher=''CricketArchive'' |title=White Conduit Club v Kent 1786 |accessdate=20 March 2013}}</ref>
As Hatch had established his reputation by 1786, he must have been active for some years previously. Very few players were mentioned by name in contemporary reports and there are no other references to Hatch.
