{{multiple issues| {{notability|date=August 2018}} {{one source|date=August 2018}} }} {{Infobox magazine | title = Jadranski Sport | logo = | logo_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_file = Jadranski sport.jpg | image_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_alt = | image_caption = Front page of the first issue | editor = [[Bogumir Doležal]] | editor_title = <!-- up to |editor_title5= --> | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = | frequency = Weekly | format = | circulation = | publisher = Split Olympic Sub-Committee | paid_circulation = | unpaid_circulation = | circulation_year = | total_circulation = | founder = | founded = | firstdate = {{Start date and age|1920|10|16}} | finaldate = {{End date|1923|04|12}} | finalnumber = | company = | country = [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia|Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]] | based = [[Split, Croatia|Split]] | language = [[Croatian language|Croatian]] | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | issn = | oclc = }} '''''Jadranski Sport''''' ({{lang-en|Adriatic Sport}}) was a weekly [[sports magazine]] published in [[Split, Croatia|Split]], then part of the [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia|Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]]. Published by the Split Olympic Sub-Committee, for the first nine issues it was published as an independent weekly, while after the tenth issue it was published as a weekly [[Supplement (publishing)|supplement]] to the ''Novo doba'' daily newspaper. The magazine's [[editor-in-chief|editor]] was [[Bogumir Doležal]].{{sfn|Jadranski Sport}}
